description:
Job Responsibilities: 

Serve as key technical interface with customer during the entire product life cycle from quotation, project transfer, NPI and mass production;
Serve as the technical coordinator for internal engineering departments including component, SMT, manufacturing, industrial, quality engineering and R&D;
Take lead to resolve technical issues and perform failure analysis during NPI and at Mass Production;
Support Project Manager to communicate technically with customers and internally with team members;
Prepare, approve and maintain engineering documents, including BOM, ECN, DN, QPL, part drawing, first article evaluation report, etc.;
Support Purchasing Department and Quality Assurance Team for supplier selection;
Support Purchasing Department to source the alternative materials;
Provide training and support to the team members.

Qualification:

Bachelor’s degree in Electronics Engineering;
Minimum 10 years engineering management experience with circuit design knowledge in Industrial, Automotive, Telecommunication and/or RF Wireless; products;
Capable to handle Failure Analysis;
Strong communication skills in both verbal and written English;
Station in Shenzhen plant is required.

Interested candidates, please contact us at 65368175 for company details before applying.

Our client is an award-winning market leader in manufacturing operating offices across the world. To cope with the expansion of the business, they are seeking for a high-caliber individual to join their expanding team.

Job Responsibilities: 

Responsible for managing project development from design stage to mass production, handling product cost evaluation,
Performing feasibility study.
Supervise Engineering Team, resource & job arrangement for the project team.

Job Requirements:

Higher Diploma/Degree in Manufacturing, Mechanical, Electronic , Industrial Engineering or related;
At least 3 year experience in OEM/ODM product development & project follow-up with consumer product manufacturing company;
Strong product design and construction senses;
Good knowledge of 3D program and AutoCAD; 
Mature, independent, analytical mind and under pressure;
Good command of spoken & written English & Mandarin.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for material management, including but not limited to inventory management, material planning and control, material expediting with the aim to ensure sufficient materials can timely meet with production needs;
Ensure company policies, guidelines and statutory requirements are fully complied;
Maintain accurate planning parameters for ERP;
Administer and optimize VMI and Buffer Stock at Suppliers;
Ensure materials are available on time to meet customer demands with direct expediting on suppliers for on time deliveries;
Minimize excesses and obsolescence through immediate actions on supplies as response to changes on demand;
Continuous improvements in inventory turns;
Monitor and control material usage variances;
Manage and enhance team performance to meet with business objectives and ensure required results can be achieved effectively and efficiently;
Lead and train subordinate.

 Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Materials Logistics Management or related discipline;
Minimum of 10 years of experience in material planning and control, warehousing and customs & logistics in EMS industry with at least 5 years at managerial level;
Knowledgeable in TS16949, SPC, ISO9000, ISO14001/OHSAS18001 and EHS documents control;
Experience in working with component suppliers;
Strong leadership and communication skills;
Good command of spoken and written English and Putonghua;
Stationed in Shenzhen is required.
Interested candidates, please contact us at 92694375 for company details before applying.

Principal Responsibilities
崗位職責

Perform inspections, maintenance and repairs on electric overhead travelling crane and lifting hoist at various customers site;
對各客戶現場的橋式起重機及電動葫蘆進行檢查、維護和維修；
 Consult with customer regarding all repair and safety related issues and discuss recommendations;
就所有與維修和安全相關的問題與客戶協商，並討論建議；
Complete and Submit service documentation. Field-initiated OQ(operative quote) or sales leads;
完成並遞交服務報告文件，現場發起有效的報價需求或銷售需求；
Other duties as assigned by supervisor.
完成上級分配的其他工作。

Key Requirements: Education/Working Experience/Professional Experience/Behavioural Competencies
任職要求：教育/工作年限/專業技能/個性要求

Above 3 years’ experience involving electrical trouble shooting and mechanic repair. Prior experience with cranes maintenance is preferred;
3年以上電氣故障排除和機械維修經驗，起重機維修/使用經驗者優先；

Have certificate of Electrical Worker must be registered with the Electrical and Mechanical Service Department(EMSD);
擁有在機電工程署(EMSD)註冊的香港電工證；

Good command of Cantonese, English and Mandarin;
流利粵語、英語、普通話；

Responsibilities:

To monitor build progress, oversee finance and ensure project quality to meet the contractual and internal requirement;
To strengthen and develop practical communication and document protocol;
To coordinate both external and internal resources to meet with project schedule;
To make strategic decisions and providing leadership and direction to project managers to implement those decisions;
To ensure all projects are delivered on-time, within scope and within budget;
To assist in the definition of project scope and objectives;
To ensure resources availability and allocation;
To develop detailed project plan to monitor and track progress;
To manage changes to project scope, schedule, and costs;
To measure project performance;
To perform risk management to minimize project risks;
To establish and maintain relationships with all relevant stakeholders

Requirements:

Degree or above in Civil / Environmental / Electrical /  Mechanical / Building Services Engineering or relevant discipline;
At least 15 years experience in managing projects;
Chartered Engineer in E&M discipline with experience on plant design are definite advantage;
Self-motivated and good communication skills; 
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese.

We offer attractive remuneration package, bonus, free lunch and excellent career prospects to the right candidate.  Interested parties please send full resume with present and salary expected to Human Resources Department, Dunwell Group, 8 Wang Lee Street, Yuen Long Industrial Estate, Yuen Long or by fax 2789-3346.

 (All information received will be kept in strictly confidential and only for recruitment-related purposes)

Established since 1978, Wing Keung Industrial International Ltd. upholds the business philosophy and vision to provide finest quality technology and contract manufacturing services that exact the customers' needs.
Over the past decades, we specialize in the manufacture of whisker parts and other metal or overmoulded plastic parts for small domestic appliances. As the company acquired an impressive wealth of knowledge and experience, our products today are exported and well acknowledged among the European markets. We supply essential parts to many of the reputed home appliance brand names including Philips, Kenwood and DeLonghi, SEB Groupe, Severin, Bosch and Siemens.

Our company is currently recruiting the following post:istant Project Engineer

 Responsibilities:

Responsible for product management & monitoring production process;
Transfer and explain client’s requirement and request to responsible personnel in China manufacturing plant
Plan and prepare necessary quality or engineering related documentations for clients or colleague in China either in Chinese or English
Knowledge of daily management and lean concepts is preferred
Assist Project Manager if needed

Requirements:

University Degree or Higher Diploma in Mechanical/Industrial/Manufacturing Engineering or any related disciplines;
Project management experience or relevant experience would be preferable;
Proficient in spoken and written English, Putonghua and Cantonese;
Reporting to Project Engineer the incumbent will be responsible for critical project activities, such as technical submissions, planning manufacturing schedule and procurement of materials;
Decent presentation skills and able to interact with customers in a face-to-face conversation;
Able to frequent travels to Mainland China to monitor production and perform goods inspection (2- 3 days per week in PRC is required)(Temporary no need to travel to PRC until the epidemic to be stable);
We are looking for critical thinkers, problem solvers and decision makers;
Experience in plastic injection or tooling or metal manufacturing process is at advantage
Our Company offers 5-days of work, competitive remuneration package and generous fringe benefits to suitable candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume, stating expected salary and availability date, to us


